  "texts": [
    "Hence, electromagnetic transient (EMT) modeling, using tools such as EMTP or PSCAD, is required for capturing the fast, high-frequency responses of these AI facilities, which may not be accurately represented by conventional phasor-domain models [121], [122].",
    "A recent dynamic load model tailored for AI data centers is proposed in [123] that incorporates three key features, including an upstream UPS, cooling loads represented by induction motor dynamics, and pulsing compute loads to represent AI workload transients.",
    "Complementary approaches include hierarchical and hybrid modeling frameworks that combine high-fidelity EMT simulations for critical components with reduced-order equivalents for external network regions.",
    "This method balances computational efficiency with accuracy, enabling reliable simulation of real-world grid impacts from AI data center behavior [124], [125].3) Tailored Demand Response Program Design: To effectively harness the flexibility of AI data centers while minimizing adverse operational impacts, grid operators need to design demand response (DR) programs specifically tailored to the unique characteristics of these loads.",
    "Standard price-based DR mechanisms, while widely used in residential and industrial contexts, may introduce new challenges when applied directly to large-scale AI loads."
  ],
